Male genitalia
(
Fig. 72
) with long uncus, approximately digitiform (
Fig. 3
); valva characteristically spinulose at costa and apex (most important diagnostic character for 

R. nesam

, not present in any other western Palearctic 

Rhodostrophia
species

); sacculus tongue-shaped, curved interiorly. Juxta wide, elongated dorso-ventrally. Aedeagus medially angled to nearly 90°; vesica membranous, without cornuti. Male sternite A8 bilobed (
Fig. 72c
), with small octavals.
